---
layout: base.njk
title: "Civic Briefs Archive"
description: "Published civic insight briefs from AI TownSquare sessions worldwide. Searchable by city, sector, and theme."
permalink: /briefs/
extraCss:
  - /css/pages/briefs.css
extraJs:
  - /js/pages/briefs-search.js
---

<!-- ============================================
     HERO
     ============================================ -->
<section class="briefs-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="label label--accent reveal">Published Insights</span>
    <h1 class="briefs-hero-title reveal">Civic Briefs Archive</h1>
    <p class="briefs-hero-sub reveal">
      Every AI TownSquare session produces a published Civic Brief within 48 hours. Search and explore the growing archive of civic intelligence on AI readiness. <a href="/protocol/">Learn how Civic Briefs are created</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================
     VIEW TOGGLE & SEARCH
     ============================================ -->
<section class="briefs-controls">
  <div class="container">
    <!-- View Toggle: Briefs | Questions -->
    <div class="briefs-view-toggle">
      <button class="briefs-view-btn briefs-view-btn--active" data-view="briefs">
        <span class="briefs-view-icon">&#9638;</span>
        Briefs
      </button>
      <button class="briefs-view-btn" data-view="questions">
        <span class="briefs-view-icon">?</span>
        Questions
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="briefs-search-wrap" id="briefsSearchWrap">
      <input
        type="text"
        class="briefs-search"
        id="briefsSearch"
        placeholder="Search by title, city, theme, or sector..."
        aria-label="Search briefs"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="briefs-filters" id="briefsFilters">
      <button class="briefs-filter-chip briefs-filter-chip--active" data-filter="All">All</button>
      <button class="briefs-filter-chip" data-filter="Healthcare">Healthcare</button>
      <button class="briefs-filter-chip" data-filter="Finance">Finance</button>
      <button class="briefs-filter-chip" data-filter="Government">Government</button>
      <button class="briefs-filter-chip" data-filter="Education">Education</button>
      <button class="briefs-filter-chip" data-filter="Cross-Sector">Cross-Sector</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================
     BRIEFS GRID
     ============================================ -->
<section class="briefs-grid-section" id="briefsView">
  <div class="container">
    {% if briefs.briefs.length > 0 %}
    <div class="briefs-grid">
      {% for brief in briefs.briefs %}
      <div class="brief-card"
           data-title="{{ brief.title }}"
           data-city="{{ brief.city }}"
           data-sector="{{ brief.sector }}"
           data-themes="{{ brief.themes | join(', ') }}">
        <div class="brief-card-meta">
          <span class="brief-card-city">{{ brief.city }}</span>
          <span>{{ brief.date }}</span>
          <span>{{ brief.sector }}</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="brief-card-title">{{ brief.title }}</h3>
        <p class="brief-card-insight">{{ brief.insight }}</p>
        <div class="brief-card-tags">
          {% for theme in brief.themes %}
          <span class="brief-card-tag">{{ theme }}</span>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
        <a href="{{ brief.link }}" class="brief-card-link">Read Brief <span>&rarr;</span></a>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% else %}
    <div class="briefs-empty-state">
      <div class="briefs-empty-content">
        <h3 class="briefs-empty-title">No Civic Briefs Published Yet</h3>
        <p class="briefs-empty-text">
          Our first Civic Brief will be published within 48 hours of the Dubai Node session on 3 April 2026.
          Each brief captures the key themes, direct quotes, and actionable signals from our structured dialogues.
          Briefs feed directly into the <a href="/sri/">Societal Readiness Index</a>.
        </p>
        <a href="/dubai/#register" class="btn btn--primary">
          Apply for Dubai Node
          <span class="btn-arrow">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================
     QUESTIONS ARCHIVE
     ============================================ -->
<section class="questions-grid-section" id="questionsView" style="display: none;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="questions-intro">
      <p class="questions-intro-text">
        Every AI TownSquare session examines one central question. These are not rhetorical; they are genuinely unresolved problems that require diverse perspectives to address.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="questions-list">
      <!-- Upcoming Question -->
      <div class="question-card question-card--upcoming">
        <div class="question-card-status">
          <span class="question-status-badge question-status-badge--upcoming">Upcoming</span>
          <span class="question-card-meta">Dubai &middot; 3 April 2026</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="question-card-text">&ldquo;Is AI going to take our jobs &mdash; or is that the wrong question entirely?&rdquo;</h3>
        <div class="question-card-sectors">
          <span class="question-sector-tag">Cross-Sector</span>
          <span class="question-sector-tag">Employment</span>
          <span class="question-sector-tag">Technology</span>
        </div>
        <div class="question-card-cta">
          <a href="/dubai/#register" class="btn btn--primary btn--sm">
            Join This Dialogue
            <span class="btn-arrow">&rarr;</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Future Questions Placeholder -->
      <div class="questions-future">
        <h4 class="questions-future-title">Future Questions</h4>
        <p class="questions-future-text">
          Questions for upcoming sessions are developed through a curation process that considers: urgency, cross-sector relevance, genuine uncertainty, and institutional impact.
        </p>
        <a href="/institute/" class="questions-future-link">Learn about question design at the Institute &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Propose a Question -->
      <div class="question-propose">
        <h4 class="question-propose-title">Propose a Question</h4>
        <p class="question-propose-text">
          Have a question that requires diverse perspectives to answer? Questions must pass three tests: (1) No single expert can answer it alone, (2) It affects multiple sectors differently, (3) Reasonable people disagree.
        </p>
        <a href="mailto:questions@aitownsquare.org?subject=Question%20Proposal" class="btn btn--outline btn--sm">
          Submit a Question
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

